Repost from: @johnkennedyvaughan 
So then what is truly best for someone else?  I suggest it’s for them to live a loving life...a selfless life.  Gods word tells us what is best for everyone.  If it’s not best for everyone it’s not best for anyone.  So what then is love if God is love...it’s all in The Right Fight.  How to live a loving life.  If you have not already... please read it.  Not my truths just the truth that set me free and will set you free.  It’s all Jesus.  1 John 4:7-12  Beloved, let us love one another, for love is from God, and whoever loves has been born of God and knows God. Anyone who does not love does not know God, because God is love. In this the love of God was made manifest among us, that God sent his only Son into the world, so that we might live through him. In this is love, not that we have loved God but that he loved us and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins. Beloved, if God so loved us, we also ought to love one another.  No one has ever seen God; if we love one another, God abides in us and his love is perfected in us.

It’s the one thing that if we don’t understand undermines everything else.  If this doesn’t make sense please read “The Right Fight” how to live a loving life.  Available on amazon or at shieldsofstrength.com 
2 Timothy 3:1 There will be terrible times in the last days. People will be lovers of themselves , lovers of money...

Repost By @johnkennedyvaughan: 
Proverbs 27:6 Wounds from a friend can be trusted, but an enemy multiplies kisses.
Anyone who helps you justify a selfish action is using you not loving you.  If someone is using you they will do anything they can to get what they want from you.  If someone loves you they will give all they have for what is truly best for you.  If it’s best for you they are in....if not they are out.

Repost By @johnkennedyvaughan: 
It’s ok to celebrate and to suffer from our past for a season but at some point we must move on and let God use what we experienced to take us to a new place.  He’s not done with you yet!  1 Corinthians 2:9 Eye has not seen, nor ear heard,Nor have entered into the heart of man. The things which God has prepared for those who love Him.  Jeremiah 29:11 for I know the plans I have for you declares the Lord.  Plans to prosper you not to harm you.  To give you a future and a hope.

Repost By @johnkennedyvaughan: 
Love does what is “truly” best for others without regard for itself.  If we don’t speak needed truth into someone’s life because we are afraid they will no longer like or love us then we are not loving them at all.  We are loving ourself.  One of the biggest mistakes I see parents make in the name of love is not being willing to hurt their child’s feelings in order to help them.  A child knows they are loved by how we are willing to love them.  If we let them get away with selfishness they know we are not loving them.  The closest moments with my own children came after their punishments were over and I made sure they knew why I wouldn’t let them be selfish.  It’s was for them not for me.  Those were the longest and best hugs ever.  Hebrews 12:6 because the Lord disciplines the one he loves, and he chastens everyone he accepts as his son.

Repost By @johnkennedyvaughan: 
Never ignore any of these truths... in your own life or others.  Because of Jesus we are family!  1 Corinthians 13:4-7 Love is patient, love is kind. It does not envy, it does not boast, it is not proud. It does not dishonor others, it is not self-seeking, it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs. Love does not delight in evil but rejoices with the truth. It always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always perseveres.
